            <term xml:id="term-k000249-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">tiaojin douke</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000249-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">挑金斗科</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000249-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">挑金斗科</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000249-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">tiāojīn dǒukē</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000249-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">t'iao-chin tou-k'o</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000249</idno>
            <note type="Note"><p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000249-1">Tiaojindouke 挑金斗科, literally “propping gold bracket set” is one of the bracket set (dougong <term ref="/keyword/k000019">斗栱</term> or douke <term ref="/keyword/k000247">斗科</term>) types used in <term ref="/keyword/k000051">Ming</term> and <term ref="/keyword/k000070">Qing</term> dynasty official architecture and can be used as an intercolumnar (pingshenke 平身科), corner (jiaoke 角科), and/or pillar top (zhutouke 柱头科) bracket sets (Gongbu 1734, 28.15b-18a). Here the word tiao 挑 means to prop up (Hanyu dacidian), and jin 金 in this case refers to the lowest interior purlin (xiajinheng 下金桁). According to the Qing dynasty court building manual Gongcheng zuofa《工程做法》(1734), tiaojin douke is a bracket set that connects the eaves purlin (yanheng 檐桁) to the interior purlin (jinheng 金桁) via one or more slanted timber bars (chenggan 秤杆) (Gongbu 1734, 29.32a-33b).  The slanted timber bar echoes the form of the Song dynasty xia’ang <term ref="/keyword/k000178">下昂</term>, but it functions less for roof load transfer and more as a stabilizing component locking the eaves to the interior structure. The structure is similar to that of the liujin douke <term ref="/keyword/k000248">溜金斗科</term>, but it differs in the following two ways: 1) the rear end of the chenggan supports the huatai bracket set (huataike 花台科) instead of being supported by it; 2) instead of being supported by a squared beam (huataifang 花台枋), the huatai bracket set and the slanted timber bar are connected from the bottom by a wooden peg called fulianshao 伏蓮捎. Modern scholars refer to the tiaojin douke 挑金斗科 and the liujin douke 溜金斗科 collectively as the liujin dougong 溜金斗栱 (Liang 1981, 108).</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000249-1">挑金斗科，是<term ref="/keyword/k000051">明</term><term ref="/keyword/k000070">清</term>官式建築中的一種<term ref="/keyword/k000019">斗栱</term>類型，可用作平身科、柱头科、角科（工部 1734，28·15b-18a）。“挑”有揚起、舉起的意思（数字版漢語大辭典），“金”指金桁。根據清工部《工程做法》，挑金斗科指以斜向構件聯系簷桁和金桁的斗栱（工部 1734，29·32a-33b）。秤桿在形式上類似於宋式斗栱中的昂，但其主要作用是將簷口與內部屋架結構穩固的連接，而不是傳遞屋面荷載。挑金斗科做法與溜金斗科相似，但有以下兩點區別：（1）秤桿後尾支撐花臺科，而不是被花臺科承托；（2）秤桿後尾與花臺科由伏蓮捎連接固定，而不是由花臺枋承托。現代學者多將挑金斗栱和溜金斗栱統稱為溜金斗栱（梁 1981，108）。</p>
